              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(diminutive of {L:παῖς&lt;SDBG:παῖς:000000&gt;}[a] ‘child,’ {D:9.41}, but in the NT παιδάριον has seemingly lost at least most of this diminutive force, but may have retained some implications of affectionate concern or interest) a child, normally below the age of puberty</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>child</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Note that παιδάριον in {S:04300600900004} denotes merely a child; it is the referential pronoun ὅς which indicates masculine gender, and therefore one may translate ‘boy.’|It is also possible that in this context the diminutive παιδάριον carries some connotation of endearment.</Comments>
